Please enable JavaScript The renovation works of the Four Seasons Hotel Riyadh at Kingdom Centre in Saudi Arabia have been completed after approximately 18 months of implementation. Following the completion of these works the hotel has unveiled Kingdom Suite, its “Signature Suite”. These new duplex suite spans from the 48th to the 50th floor of the hotel building. The suite guarantees an exquisite view of the city and 330 meters squared of palatial space to guests. Within its main living area, the suite hosts an impressive contemporary ceiling pendant. Additionally, the Kingdom Suite at Four Seasons Hotel Riyadh features a 146-inch modular TV screen. The screen comprises 16 Samsung LEDs. Further enabling guests to enjoy their favorite motion pictures. The suite’s design features color tones of soft blues and rust characteristics. Additionally, it includes curated Saudi objects of art through Alwaleed Philanthropies. Also Read: 501-Unit Residential Villa Project in Tabouk City, Saudi Arabia Launched In addition to an elegant touch of luxury, the Kingdom Suite offers guests dedicated butler service, upon booking. Therefore, guests will receive personalized services as well as attention to all requests. The Senior General Manager at The Four Seasons Hotel commented on the Kingdom Suite at Four Seasons Hotel Riyadh project. Guenter Gebhard stated that the Kingdom suite’s design aims to engage with the guests’ senses. Moreover, he continued, the suite’s design also aims to create eloquent visual narratives that guests will remember long after their stay. Guenter Gebhard concluded by saying that the Signature Suite prioritizes offering guests the ultimate in luxury. Furthermore, it aims to offer guests the opportunity to take time to connect with family and/or friends as well as timely experiences. In addition to the Kingdom Suite the penthouse suite has been a highly anticipated addition to the Four Seasons portfolio.